Join Artizan Coffee Company, a leader in the Organic Specialty Coffee Industry. We are looking for a talented Senior PPC Ad Manager to elevate our product listings and drive customer engagement. This remote position allows you to work from the comfort of your own home while contributing to the success of our business in the online retail space. Working hours will be from Monday to Friday, 9 AM to 5 PM / New York EST GMT-5

As the Senior Manager, PPC Advertising you will be responsible in leading our paid team and manage eCommerce ad campaigns across a variety of platforms. You'll leverage your expertise in Google Ads, Facebook Ads, and Amazon Ads while also handling campaigns on paid search, paid social, display, marketplace, retail media, CTV, and more. You'll be responsible for handling multiple projects with accuracy and super-fast execution in a fast-paced, ever-changing environment, with a focus on driving sales and profits.

This role requires a hands-on approach--actively managing campaigns and utilizing Excel--rather than simply delegating or attending meetings. You'll also provide guidance and support to your team, ensuring that projects are completed accurately and swiftly. Quick problem-solving and continuous process improvement are essential, along with maintaining timely communication and following up to ensure all deadlines are met.

DUTIES AND RESPONSIBILITIES:

Advertising Campaign Management

1. Oversee and manage the daily operations of campaign creation, optimization, A/B testing, and maintenance across various platforms, including Amazon Ads, Google Ads, Meta (Facebook/Instagram) Ads, Microsoft Advertising, and Retail Media accounts, ensuring alignment with KPIs and all reporting and paid advertising management are carefully executed with the highest quality and in a timely manner;

2. Manage and monitor bids and budgets on a daily, weekly, and monthly basis, and track key performance indicators for campaigns;

3. Take the lead in setting up and launching new accounts, including all aspects of account creation, monitoring, expansion, and optimization;

4. Direct the optimization of Google and Bing Merchant Centers product feeds to drive strategic growth and effectiveness in Shopping Campaigns;

5. Take charge of all testing methodologies within paid media, covering areas such as bidding strategies, audience targeting, ad copy, and landing page performance;

6. Quickly investigate and resolve issues that adversely impact performance or cause ads to stop serving during and outside normal working hours;

7. Create comprehensive reports to showcase optimizations, A/B tests, performance metrics, and effectively communicate findings and strategies to company leadership;

8. Utilize extensive expertise in paid media platforms to analyze and resolve a wide range of diverse and complex issues effectively;

9. Partner closely with the creative team to develop engaging content, images, and videos that drive sales and high conversion rates. We like direct response copy that grabs attention, persuades, and converts.

10. Strategize, plan, and execute SEO, pay-per-click, social media, display, inbound and outbound marketing campaigns.

11. Develop optimization strategies that increase the company’s website search engine results rankings.

12. Actively work to improve site speed and page ranking


Special Projects and Ad Hoc Requests

1. Assist with special projects and ad hoc requests as needed to support the advertising department;

2. Contribute to the development of digital media plan options and recommendations;

3. Stay current with emerging digital marketing trends and identify opportunities to incorporate them into client strategies;

4. Work Eastern Standard Time Zone;

5. Follow company standards to maintain integrity, client focus, teamwork, and respect for everyone in every interaction;

6. Exhibit a sense of urgency in the execution of all job functions and delivery expectations, especially around established deadlines;

7. Perform other duties as assigned.

QUALIFICATIONS

Required

Advertising Campaign Management

1. Over 5 years of hands-on management experience in overseeing Paid Search, Shopping, Social, Display, Amazon, Retail Media, and Native advertising platforms; 

2. Bachelor’s Degree (or higher) in Marketing, Computer Sciences, Quantitative Field (Statistics) Business Administration or a related field. Experience in Search Engine Marketing (SEM) and Paid Search (PPC).

3. Solid experience with website analysis using a variety of analytics tools including Google Analytics, SEMRush, ahrefs, Uber suggest and other industry platforms Proficiency in Google, Bing, Meta, Amazon and Walmart Ads manager.

3. Proven track record of delivering measurable results through performance-driven paid media campaigns;

4. Experience across various CMS platforms such as Wordpress, Magento, Shopify, Squarespace etc.

3. Advanced skills in Excel and a thorough understanding of Google Analytics;

4. Great attention to detail and strong data analysis skills to ensure campaigns run smoothly and uncover insights for improving campaign performance.


QUALIFICATIONS:

Preferred

1. Proven ability to independently manage multiple priorities and projects, while effectively communicating and collaborating with stakeholders across the board;

2. Strong communication and presentation skills, proficiently translating complex data into actionable insights with clarity and precision;

3. Team-oriented leadership style, skilled in delegation and organization, readily offering support to colleagues as required;

4. Exceptional creative thinking skills, adept at problem-solving and consistently achieving growth targets;

5. Startup mindset, adept at multitasking and executing in fast-paced, dynamic environments;

6. Must have high attention to detail, numbers, proofreading, writing, and editing skills for accuracy;

7. Expertise in implementing, managing, and optimizing multi-channel paid media campaigns across various digital advertising platforms.

8. Working knowledge in JavaScript/ jQuery, PHP, HTML, and programming languages as it pertains to SEO is an advantage.

9. Google certification/GAPP (Google Analtyics Platform Principles) certification is a plus.

10. Experience in a B2B, International and/or multi-region company is a plus.

11. Working knowledge in JavaScript/ jQuery, PHP, HTML, and programming languages as it pertains to SEO is an advantage

Personal

1. Excellent verbal and written English communication and presentation skills;

2. Proficiency in preparation and presentation of creative work;

3. Extremely organized with ability to prioritize work activities;

4. Excellent time management skills with a proven ability to meet deadlines;

5. Keen attention to detail, solution oriented, and resolution focused;

6. Strong interpersonal skills; able to listen and work well with others on the team;

7. Willing to take ownership of a presented problem or issue through resolution;

8. Ability to work independently and under own initiative;

9. Ability to prioritize, multi-task, and coordinate workloads;

10. Ability to function well in a fast-paced environment and balancing multiple projects simultaneously; and

11. Ability to adapt to change in a rapid-paced environment, manage demands, and learn new technology systems.

Job Types: Full-time, Permanent

